  <head>
    
    <meta charset="UTF-8" >
    <!-- this meta is used because the character encoding was not declared. 
     UTF-8 is a widely supported and versatile encoding standard that covers almost all characters and symbols in the world.
     This declaration informs the browser of the character encoding used in the document, ensuring correct rendering of characters and symbols.-->


     <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
     

    <title>
      this is my first web page
      
</title>
    <!-- this line is used for heading on the top of the web page that will not be displayed on the web page but it will displayed on the top
      of the webpage as a heading of website -->


      <link rel="icon" href="img.png" type="image/icon">
    
     <!-- link is used to link some other language file into it to make it better and rel is relation href is hypertext refrence 
      itâ€™s an HTML attribute used to create a link to another page, file, email address, or location within the same page. -->


                                                                      
